cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

The paper deals with computer vision and image processing, specifically the recovery of hidden scenes from indirect illumination in nearby visible regions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of video data suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
